@ResetClock
Feature: Rental Cost Calculation
  As a system
  I want to calculate final rental cost based on actual duration
  So that I can determine the total amount to charge with forgiveness rule and overtime charges

  Background:
    Given the request header "Content-Type" is "application/vnd.bikerental.v1+json"
    And the following tariff records exist in db
      | id | name        | description     | equipmentType | basePrice | halfHourPrice | hourPrice | dayPrice | discountedPrice | validFrom  | validTo    | status |
      | 1  | Hourly Rate | Standard hourly | bicycle       | 100.00    | 60.00         | 100.00    | 500.00   | 90.00           | 2026-01-01 | 2026-12-31 | ACTIVE |

  Scenario Outline: Calculate cost for on-time or early return
    Given now is "<startTime>"
    And a rental exists with
      | tariffId | startedAt   | plannedDurationMinutes |
      | 1        | <startTime> | <plannedMinutes>       |
    When the rental is returned at "<returnTime>"
    Then the final cost calculation should be
      | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost | forgivenessApplied | messagePattern |
      | <baseCost> | 0.00       | <baseCost> | true              | On time       |
    Examples:
      | startTime           | returnTime          | plannedMinutes | baseCost |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T10:55:00 | 60             | 100.00   |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T10:30:00 | 60             | 100.00   |

  Scenario Outline: Calculate cost with forgiveness applied
    Given now is "<startTime>"
    And a rental exists with
      | tariffId | startedAt   | plannedDurationMinutes |
      | 1        | <startTime> | <plannedMinutes>       |
    When the rental is returned at "<returnTime>"
    Then the final cost calculation should be
      | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost | forgivenessApplied | messagePattern |
      | <baseCost> | 0.00       | <baseCost> | true              | Forgiven      |
    Examples:
      | startTime           | returnTime          | plannedMinutes | overtimeMinutes | baseCost |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T11:05:00 | 60             | 5               | 100.00   |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T11:07:00 | 60             | 7               | 100.00   |

  Scenario Outline: Calculate cost with overtime charges
    Given now is "<startTime>"
    And a rental exists with
      | tariffId | startedAt   | plannedDurationMinutes |
      | 1        | <startTime> | <plannedMinutes>       |
    When the rental is returned at "<returnTime>"
    Then the final cost calculation should be
      | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost | forgivenessApplied | messagePattern |
      | <baseCost> | <overtimeCost> | <totalCost> | false             | Overtime charged |
    Examples:
      | startTime           | returnTime          | plannedMinutes | overtimeMinutes | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T11:08:00 | 60             | 8               | 100.00   | 8.33         | 108.33    |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T11:10:00 | 60             | 10              | 100.00   | 8.33         | 108.33    |
      | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 2026-02-24T11:15:00 | 60             | 15              | 100.00   | 16.67        | 116.67    |

  Scenario: Calculate cost for half-hour rental period
    Given now is "2026-02-24T10:00:00"
    And a rental exists with
      | tariffId | startedAt           | plannedDurationMinutes |
      | 1        | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 30                     |
    When the rental is returned at "2026-02-24T10:35:00"
    Then the final cost calculation should be
      | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost | forgivenessApplied | messagePattern |
      | 60.00    | 0.00         | 60.00     | true               | Forgiven       |

  Scenario: Calculate cost for day rental period
    Given now is "2026-02-24T10:00:00"
    And a rental exists with
      | tariffId | startedAt           | plannedDurationMinutes |
      | 1        | 2026-02-24T10:00:00 | 300                    |
    When the rental is returned at "2026-02-24T15:10:00"
    Then the final cost calculation should be
      | baseCost | overtimeCost | totalCost | forgivenessApplied | messagePattern |
      | 500.00   | 0.00         | 500.00     | true               | Forgiven       |
